            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1513759015,
            "creation_date": 1513759015,
            "body": "<p>May be you know this thing. But for others I would re-iterate. There is difference between compile time error and run time error. When we compile it, what java compiler does is to check for syntax errors and if no syntax error is present then it would create a .class file out of it. If any syntactical error is there then the code will not compile. Whereas in runtime/execution errors,  is an event or situation, which occurs during the execution of a program, that disrupts the normal flow of the program's instructions.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 47901800,
            "question_id": 47895335
        }
